sec.p:
Figure 3 shows the behavior under pressure inside the autoclave as a function of temperature during the hydrothermal process to synthesize the TiO2 nanoparticles, which were used when preparing the paste for screen printing of the mesoporous TiO2m layer. It can be observed from the P vs. T curve in Fig. 3 that for temperatures lower than 150 °C, the pressure falls below 7 atm. At 100 °C, the system reaches a pressure near 1 atm, and for temperatures above 150 °C, the pressure rapidly increases until it reaches a value of 81 atm at 210 °C. The abrupt growth in pressure inside the autoclave plays a fundamental role in the finite growth of the nanoparticle, as will be explained in detail in the following section. An allometric adjustment, represented in Eq. 1, allowed for adjusting of the approximate curve to the experimental data (black dot curve in Fig. 3), which is very similar to the vapor pressure curves of ammonia, water, and mercury [20].Fig. 3
